      • rolloutRestart

        void rolloutRestart()
             throws ApplyException
        Forces a rollout restart of the deployment by patching the running config file in memory with a timestamp. Restart only occurs if the patch is unique, hence why the timestamp is added.
        Throws:
        ApplyException - Throws exception if the change could not be applied.
